  "reasoning": "The nfs_lookup_revalidate function incorrectly treats signal-interrupted RPC calls (returning ERESTARTSYS) as permanent dentry invalidations. At line 1158-1161, when nfs_lookup_verify_inode returns an error (which calls __nfs_revalidate_inode that can return ERESTARTSYS from getattr RPC), the code goes to out_zap_parent which invalidates the directory and eventually returns 0 (dentry invalid). Similarly, at line 1183-1186, when the lookup RPC returns ERESTARTSYS, the code treats it as a failure and marks the dentry invalid (returns 0). ERESTARTSYS (-512) should not be treated as a permanent failure but rather returned to allow the VFS to properly handle signal-interrupted syscalls. This causes autofs mounts to disappear when the RPC is interrupted by signals during unmount/revalidation cycles."
}

